  "articleSummary": "This technical tutorial-style article details the implementation of beam search within the `transformers.js` library to replace a previously non-functional \"greedy-only\" decoding loop. The author explains the architectural transition from simple greedy selection to managing multiple candidate sequences, highlighting the necessity of a global ranking system over the library's existing local samplers. Key technical challenges discussed include the implementation of diverse beam search, the management of a `BeamHypotheses` priority queue, and the critical need to reorder Key-Value (KV) caches to maintain state consistency across beams. The intended audience is JavaScript developers and machine learning engineers interested in the internal mechanics of porting Python-based transformer features to the browser or Node.js environments.",
